# Pine Script v6 — Cursor Rules
# Maintained by Ugur Pala — mail@ugurpala.com
# github.com/trugurpala/pinescriptv6

## Before writing any Pine Script v6 code

1. Read LESSONS_LEARNED.md — never repeat a known error
2. Check LLM_MANIFEST.md — find the correct reference file for the task
3. Read the relevant reference file before writing

## Code Rules

- Every script MUST start with //@version=6
- Use ta.* functions — do not reimplement manually
- Use var/varip correctly per the execution model
- Never invent function names not in the reference docs
- No v5 syntax (study(), security() at top level, etc.)

## Error Protocol

When you solve a Pine Script v6 error:
- Update LESSONS_LEARNED.md immediately
- Format: error message, cause, fix, minimal code example

## Reference Map

| Need | File |
|------|------|
| RSI, EMA, crossover, ATR, pivot | reference/functions/ta.md |
| strategy.entry, exit, position | reference/functions/strategy.md |
| plot, line, box, label, table | reference/functions/drawing.md |
| request.security, MTF | reference/functions/request.md |
| array, map, matrix | reference/functions/collections.md |
| math, str, input, alert | reference/functions/general.md |
| open, close, bar_index | reference/variables.md |
| var, varip, barstate | concepts/execution_model.md |
| Repainting | concepts/timeframes.md |
| Errors | concepts/common_errors.md |
